# Delegation & surgical edits (operational)

Binding floor: [`.cursor/rules/00-binding-standards.mdc`](00-binding-standards.mdc) + `CLAUDE.md` § Agent workflow. Full routing: [`.claude/skills/cavecrew/SKILL.md`](../../.claude/skills/cavecrew/SKILL.md).

Cursor **Task** tool = subagent spawn. Prefer subagents over ad-hoc bulk shell scripts on source files.

## Routing (default)

| Task | Subagent / skill |
|------|------------------|
| Domain feature / fix / multi-layer logic | **`business-logic-shield`** first ([`.claude/skills/business-logic-shield/SKILL.md`](../../.claude/skills/business-logic-shield/SKILL.md)); rule [35-business-logic-shield.mdc](35-business-logic-shield.mdc) |
| Locate symbol / callers | `cavecrew-investigator` (default); `explore` for prose |
| Fix ≤2 files | `cavecrew-builder` or main `Edit` after `Read` |
| Review diff/PR | `cavecrew-reviewer`; `bugbot` / `security-review` on request |
| Fix 3+ files | Main plan → parallel investigator/builder per file |
| `/gsd:*` phase work | `gsd-*` per workflow; trivial → inline (`/gsd:fast`) |

## Hard stops

- No ad-hoc `sed -i`, `awk`, `perl -pi`, `python -c/-e`, `node -e` replace on `apps/`, `packages/`, `prisma/`, `.planning/`
- No agent helper scripts (`fix-*.ts`, `bulk-rename.sh`) unless user asks
- After spawning on a scope: **do not** read/edit that scope in parallel — wait for result

## Allowed shell

- `pnpm` / `npm run` / `turbo` project scripts
- Read-only `git`
- Test / typecheck runners
- Existing repo codemods (`scripts/`, jscodeshift) with user approval

PreToolUse advisory: `.claude/hooks/no-bulk-script-guard.js` on suspicious Bash commands.
